        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.7: \"Arcadlin Antibody Suppresses Synaptic Transmission and Blocks LTP\". Experimental description: Acute slices are of rat species: \"For in vivo LTP studies, rats were implanted bilaterally with stimulating and recording electrodes in the perforant path and the hilus of the dentate gyrus as described previously (19). For in vitro LTP studies, hippocampal slices (500 μm) were prepared from rats (100-200 g) as described elsewhere (\"" ;
